listen to this song because it speaks to the hope that love can be salvaged even in the face of heartbreak. I Will Always Love You – Whitney Houston (1992) – Written by Dolly Parton. Used in the film “The Bodyguard” (1992). This song is about the pain of letting go of someone you love and accepting that they may never return. People listen to this song because it is a classic expression of the heartache of lost love. Unbreak My Heart – Toni Braxton (1996) – Written by Diane Warren. Used in the film “Mystery, Alaska” (1999). This song is about begging someone to come back and fix a broken heart. People listen to this song because it expresses the desire to hold on to love even when it is lost. We Found Love – Rihanna ft. Calvin Harris (2011) – Written by Calvin Harris and Rihanna. Used in the film “This Is 40” (2012). This song is about the intense feelings of love and the pain of loss. People listen to this song because it speaks to the rollercoaster of emotions that come with heartbreak. Cry Me a River – Justin Timberlake (2002) – Written by Justin Timberlake, Scott Storch, and Tim Mosley. Used in the film “Dawn of the Dead” (2004). This song is about feeling betrayed by someone you loved and the anger and pain that follows. People listen to this song because it speaks to the anger and frustration that often come with heartbreak. A Thousand Years – Christina Perri (2011) – Written by Christina Perri. Used in the film “The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn Part 1” (2011). This song is about the longing and pain of being separated from someone you love. People listen to this song because it speaks to the depth of love and the heartache that comes with losing it. I Don’t Want to Miss a Thing – Aerosmith (1998) – Written by Diane Warren. Used in the film “Armageddon” (1998). This song is about not wanting to be away from someone you love, even for a moment. People listen to this song because it expresses the fear of losing someone and the intense feelings of love that come with that fear. My Heart Will Go On – Celine Dion (1997) – Written by James Horner and Will Jennings. Used in the film “Titanic” (1997). This song is about the love that endures even after death. People listen to this song because it speaks to the belief that love can endure even in the face of heartbreak. Someone You Loved – Lewis Capaldi (2019) – Written by Lewis Capaldi, Pete Kelleher, Tom Barnes, and Benjamin Kohn. Used in the film “Five Feet Apart” (2019). This song is about the pain of losing someone you love and the feeling of emptiness that follows. People listen to this song because it speaks to the emptiness and sadness that 